Hii friends! 👋🏻 I hope you found this video helpful for learning the basics of Goodnotes 6. There was a lot to cover so I focused on the features & tools that would give you the gist of the app (study sets + interactive math tests are not covered). Please turn on the Subtitles (English) if you want to follow along and please feel free to use the Timestamps/Chapters to jump to specific sections ♥

Timestamps/Chapters:
00:00 - Intro
00:21 - Creating an account
00:47 - Main library navigation
01:43 - What you can import
02:07 - How to create folders
02:20 - Turning on Scribble
02:41 - How to create a notebook, template/cover options
03:45 - Adding new pages
04:03 - Double-tap to fill screen
04:07 - Changing the template after notebook has been created
04:40 - Horizontal and vertical scrolling
04:54 - Stylus & palm rejection
05:18 - What's in the toolbar? (Read Only, Keyboard, Audio Recording)
07:03 - All the notetaking tools! (Pen, Highlighter, Eraser, etc.)
07:22 - Pen tool (how to use, types, presets, etc.)
09:04 - Pen gesture & writing aids
09:45 - Eraser tool (how to use, types, options, etc.)
10:19 - Highlighter tool
10:31 - Shapes tool
10:50 - Lasso tool
11:27 - Convert to text/math using Lasso
11:52 - Elements tool
12:18 - Photos tool
12:44 - Textbox tool
12:53 - How to install custom fonts into Goodnotes
14:00 - Zoom Window tool
14:59 - Ruler tool
15:16 - Laser Pointer tool
15:37 - Thumbnail view
16:22 - Search tool
16:34 - Other icons - Adding new page, bookmarking
17:09 - Sharing/exporting options
17:44 - "Three dots" menu options
18:14 - Document Editing options (including Toolbar Customization)
19:20 - Splitscreen in Goodnotes
19:31 - Cloud & backup
20:28 - Other settings from the main library
20:55 - Goodnotes pricing

I would like to tell two function tips which was key features for us to choose Goodnotes 6 over others, which you didn't mention at least on this video. First is screen share collaboration, which is unique at the moment for Goodnotes. When you share you document with co-worker, you both can see document on live and work it together. It's just superb feature to plan things with a team! 

And second is that when you record and make notes on same time, you can click&hold note and listen record on spot when you made selected note. It's very useful when you go through like 1 hour meeting notes. And also if you listen recording and add notes they will be synced and time stamped with recording also!
